## Quadratic curves

f:x→ ax^2+bx+c
f:x→ a(x-h)^2+k
$$
f:x\rightarrow a(x-x_1)(x-x_2)
$$

$$
f:x\rightarrow a(x-x_{h1})(x-x_{h2})+H
$$


## a = 1/i or -1/i, concavity

```julia
p2 = Plots.plot!(theme_dark(),xlim = (-2,2))
for i in 1:25
    Plots.plot!(x->x^2/i)
end
Plots.title!("x-> (1/ i) *(x^2);i in 1:25")
#savefig(p2,doc_dir*"/xSqrDivByi.png")
p2
```

```julia
p2 = Plots.plot!(theme_dark(),xlim = (-2,2))
for i in 1:25
    Plots.plot!(x->-x^2/i)
end
Plots.title!("x->  - (1/ i) *(x^2);i in 1:25")
#savefig(p2,doc_dir*"/-xSqrDivByi.png")
p2
```


```julia

p2 = Plots.plot!(theme_dark(),xlim = (-2,2))
anm = @animate for i in 1:25
